  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "The current `TopologyManager` only allows devices to be aligned by NUMA node. However, certain devices have internal constraints which dictate how they should be aligned when multiple devices of the same type are requested.\r\n\r\nThis issue tracks the effort to add support for such \"inter-device\" topology constraints when allocating devices to a container. The proposed solution allows each device plugin to specify preferred device allocations based on internal topology constraints, while still leaving the final allocation decision up to the `devicemanager`. \r\n\r\nKEP Update:https://github.com/kubernetes/enhancements/pull/1121\r\nImplementation PR: TBD",
